aa(lp80
VAnd then they disappear.
p81
aVLike 99 percent of all the animals that have once lived,
p82
aVthey go extinct, likely due to a warming climate
p83
aVand fast-encroaching dense forests
p84
aVthat are migrating north,
p85
aVand also, as the late, great Paul Martin once put it,
p86
aVprobably Pleistocene overkill,
