aa(lp89
VFortunately, we find millions of their remains
p90
aVstrewn across the permafrost buried deep
p91
aVin Siberia and Alaska, and we can actually go up there
p92
aVand actually take them out.
p93
aVAnd the preservation is, again,
p94
aVlike those insects in [amber], phenomenal.
p95
aVSo you have teeth, bones with blood
p96
aVwhich look like blood, you have hair,
p97
aVand you have intact carcasses or heads
p98
aVwhich still have brains in them.
