aa(lp100
VSo the preservation and the survival of DNA
p101
aVdepends on many factors, and I have to admit,
p102
aVmost of which we still don't quite understand,
p103
aVbut depending upon when an organism dies
p104
aVand how quickly he's buried, the depth of that burial,
p105
aVthe constancy of the temperature of that burial environment,
p106
aVwill ultimately dictate how long DNA will survive
p107
aVover geologically meaningful time frames.
p108
aVAnd it's probably surprising to many of you
p109
aVsitting in this room that it's not the time that matters,
p110
aVit's not the length of preservation,
p111
aVit's the consistency of the temperature of that preservation that matters most.
